8
00:00:53,620 --> 00:00:56,590
Why didn't you tell me Mom paid a visit?

9
00:00:59,450 --> 00:01:02,130
I had things to think about.

10
00:01:02,130 --> 00:01:05,130
"Think"? About what?

11
00:01:05,130 --> 00:01:09,380
About whether you should really break up with me as Mom told you to?

12
00:01:09,380 --> 00:01:10,960
No.

13
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:13,910
I should've watched more dramas.

14
00:01:13,910 --> 00:01:16,130
Money envelopes and a glass of water to the face.

15
00:01:16,130 --> 00:01:20,970
I thought I could handle those things like they do in dramas,

16
00:01:20,970 --> 00:01:24,830
but I couldn't say a single word to her.

17
00:01:26,090 --> 00:01:28,660
Did Mom speak harshly to you?

18
00:01:29,930 --> 00:01:31,250
Yes.

19
00:01:31,910 --> 00:01:36,060
She told me what we have isn't love.

20
00:01:36,060 --> 00:01:37,180
What?

21
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:39,470
You don't know how much I regretted it all night.

22
00:01:39,470 --> 00:01:41,760
Should I go to Seoul right now and tell her?

23
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:44,900
That I love you so much!

24
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:50,920
So, you're saying that you didn't tell her that, right?

25
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:52,340
What?

26
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:59,420
That's what my profound realization was about.

27
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:02,050
I love you!

28
00:02:02,050 --> 00:02:05,310
I said I love you! I love you.

29
00:02:06,980 --> 00:02:08,680
I love you.

30
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:11,820
I love you, Kim San Ha. I love you.

31
00:02:16,020 --> 00:02:17,910
Welcome.

32
00:02:25,740 --> 00:02:27,670
Have a seat.

33
00:02:27,670 --> 00:02:29,110
Yes.

34
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:51,550
I told you I'd wait until you gave us your approval.

35
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:55,510
But I came because I couldn't wait.

36
00:02:56,820 --> 00:02:59,060
Fine, go on.

37
00:03:04,220 --> 00:03:10,680
I want to make sure Joo Won keeps smiling, eats well,

38
00:03:11,490 --> 00:03:14,140
and stays happy.

39
00:03:16,230 --> 00:03:18,910
When I left Haedong ten years ago,

40
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:22,700
I promised myself that when I was truly healed

41
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:27,320
and no longer needed to lean on Joo Won,

42
00:03:27,320 --> 00:03:29,960
I would come back.

43
00:03:31,820 --> 00:03:34,320
I missed her so much every day,

44
00:03:35,030 --> 00:03:37,900
but I didn't have the courage to hide my pain...

45
00:03:39,030 --> 00:03:41,140
so I couldn't come back.

46
00:03:42,810 --> 00:03:47,790
I wanted to come back after becoming a true adult.

47
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:55,300
Is that why you endured it for 10 years and never once came back?

48
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,680
Yes.

49
00:03:58,290 --> 00:04:01,440
But in the end, I couldn't endure it

50
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:03,280
and just came back.

51
00:04:05,220 --> 00:04:08,400
Then I met Joo Won again,

52
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:11,060
came back to my family

53
00:04:12,090 --> 00:04:14,250
and everything was better.

54
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:24,580
I truly won't worry Joo Won.

55
00:04:24,580 --> 00:04:29,640
Joo Won and I will live ordinary lives like other people.

56
00:04:33,270 --> 00:04:36,260
People's lives are pretty much the same.

57
00:04:36,260 --> 00:04:38,260
What makes you different from other people?

58
00:04:38,260 --> 00:04:42,160
Who in life can avoid difficult times?

59
00:04:43,380 --> 00:04:48,370
I'll always be on Joo Won's side whenever it gets tough.

60
00:04:48,370 --> 00:04:50,530
From now on

61
00:04:50,530 --> 00:04:52,870
I won't be on your side.

62
00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:54,880
Yes.

63
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:58,010
You know how scary I get when I'm angry, right?

64
00:04:58,010 --> 00:04:59,680
I do.

65
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,740
That's enough, then.

66
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,480
Have you eaten?

67
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,400
No.

68
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:13,600
- Have a bowl of noodles before you go. 
 - Okay.

69
00:05:27,230 --> 00:05:29,820
There's a tiny basketball class next to Haedong High.

70
00:05:29,820 --> 00:05:31,450
I'm going to take it over.

71
00:05:31,450 --> 00:05:32,730
"A basketball class"?

72
00:05:32,730 --> 00:05:35,090
I played basketball in America, didn't I?

73
00:05:35,090 --> 00:05:37,990
What about your dad? What does he say?

74
00:05:37,990 --> 00:05:42,300
As for me, I support anything you want to do.

75
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,870
Dad does, too.

76
00:05:43,870 --> 00:05:46,720
He's okay with anything I do.

77
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,250
Really?

78
00:05:51,420 --> 00:05:56,530
Calling you Mom and Dad makes it feel like you really are my Mom and Dad.

79
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,500
Madam told me.

80
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:05,120
I heard you visited Dad's store yesterday.

81
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,730
Yes.

82
00:06:06,730 --> 00:06:10,310
Since you're looking into moving into that neighbourhood,

83
00:06:10,310 --> 00:06:12,900
I had a few things to ask him.

84
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:16,090
Is that right? Dad likes that neighborhood, too, right?

85
00:06:16,090 --> 00:06:17,340
Yes.

86
00:06:17,340 --> 00:06:21,910
He says you'll be at ease there.

87
00:06:24,130 --> 00:06:25,720
All right.

88
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,710
I'll take care of it, then.

89
00:06:27,710 --> 00:06:29,450
Madam's information is solid. 
    

90
00:06:29,450 --> 00:06:31,670
It seemed like that to me, too.

91
00:06:31,670 --> 00:06:34,510
You know things don't just work themselves out, right?

92
00:06:36,410 --> 00:06:39,550
Do you know what I've always regretted?

93
00:06:39,550 --> 00:06:41,500
What?

94
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:46,180
That time I opposed Ahjumma, saying I didn’t need a mom.

95
00:06:46,180 --> 00:06:50,720
 I don't need a mommy! I only need an oppa! 

96
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,910
Back then, I was too young.

97
00:06:52,910 --> 00:06:58,770
I felt really bad because I felt like I wronged Dad, Ahjumma, and you.

98
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:05,010
You were seven years old at the time.

99
00:07:05,010 --> 00:07:07,280
It's natural for a child to act like that.

100
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,990
Were you still consumed by that?

101
00:07:10,890 --> 00:07:14,080
That's just how I felt.

102
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:18,920
Wow, Yoon Joo Won is all grown up.

103
00:07:20,460 --> 00:07:23,780
So will it be Ahjumma or Dad?

104
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:26,940
It’s probably better to push Dad to take action, right?

105
00:07:26,940 --> 00:07:30,800
Isn't there a natural way to do this?

106
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,300
By chance...

107
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:36,100
Let's tell him we are going to introduce Dae Wook Ahjusshi to her.

108
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:37,900
Are you crazy?

109
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:40,210
How messed up are you trying to make our family tree?

110
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:42,380
Is that too ridiculous?

111
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:44,090
I think it's all right.

112
00:07:44,090 --> 00:07:47,360
Actually, the jealousy strategy...

113
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:50,900
doesn't seem like a bad idea.

114
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:01,610
Jae Eun set Dal up on a blind date.

115
00:08:01,610 --> 00:08:03,840
I guess that's today.

116
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:06,100
- "Blind date"? 
 - Yes.

117
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:09,450
Since Dal's mom keeps arranging blind dates for her,

118
00:08:09,450 --> 00:08:12,060
Jae Eun suggested we step in.

119
00:08:12,060 --> 00:08:14,440
We gathered all our Haedong High alumni

120
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:18,070
and arranged a blind date with someone Dal's mom would approve of.

121
00:08:19,110 --> 00:08:21,520
Did Dal agree to that?

122
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:23,770
She doesn't even like blind dates.

123
00:08:23,770 --> 00:08:25,240
Yes.

124
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:28,830
Dal is not exactly in a position to disagree.

125
00:08:28,830 --> 00:08:31,710
Since rumors about someone rejecting her have spread all over Haedong.

126
00:08:31,710 --> 00:08:34,630
She didn't get rejected!

127
00:08:46,970 --> 00:08:48,920
Thank you.

128
00:08:52,330 --> 00:08:54,400
He's a catch.

129
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:57,960
What would you like to order?

130
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,640
What would you like?

131
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,340
Your most delicious menu item.

132
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:03,290
"Delicious"?

133
00:09:04,710 --> 00:09:07,380
Why are you outside?

134
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:09,480
Someone just left.

135
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,330
Oh, they stopped by?

136
00:09:14,330 --> 00:09:15,420
Who do you think it was?

137
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:17,920
There's nothing to be shy about.

138
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:22,510
Family should be understanding about these things.

139
00:09:22,510 --> 00:09:24,260
I know everything.

140
00:09:28,190 --> 00:09:32,610
Fine. There's no parent who can win against their child. I lost.

141
00:09:32,610 --> 00:09:35,950
When I said I didn't approve of San Ha, you should've consoled the kids

142
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:38,200
and paid more attention to the family.

143
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,000
You were out of sight all this time.

144
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,740
But now that I've finally approved of San Ha,

145
00:09:41,740 --> 00:09:44,740
you're absolutely ecstatic, aren't you?

146
00:09:44,740 --> 00:09:48,340
I see, you've already approved of them.

147
00:09:48,340 --> 00:09:50,750
"Already"? "Already"?

148
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:52,210
Gosh, Mr. Yoon.

149
00:09:52,210 --> 00:09:56,810
Team Leader Kim came with a fruit basket to ask you to look favorably on San Ha.

150
00:09:56,810 --> 00:09:59,670
Team Leader Kim was really concerned, too.

151
00:09:59,670 --> 00:10:02,270
You should've told me, then. It's not like I'm God.

152
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:04,170
How would I have known?

153
00:10:05,180 --> 00:10:07,210
Well...

154
00:10:16,770 --> 00:10:20,850
How could I tell you when you were with her doing this?

155
00:10:20,850 --> 00:10:23,320
"You're light."

156
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,740
What are you talking about?

157
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:27,000
And I didn't grab her back like that.

158
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,840
I just caught her before she fell and it happened that way.

159
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,930
- Is that so? 
 - Hey...

160
00:10:33,540 --> 00:10:35,630
Now that I think about it, I had a lot of bread.

161
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:37,760
I can do without the noodles.

162
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,890
Team Leader, I'll head out first.

163
00:10:39,890 --> 00:10:44,800
Okay, sure. I'm going to leave, too.

164
00:10:45,730 --> 00:10:46,780
What?

165
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:49,870
There's food left over from San Ha's visit. Eat before you go.

166
00:10:49,870 --> 00:10:51,860
What did you make for San Ha?

167
00:10:51,860 --> 00:10:53,160
What did you make?

168
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:54,770
   

169
00:10:54,770 --> 00:10:56,320
Joo Won.

170
00:10:57,030 --> 00:10:58,590
Why?

171
00:10:58,590 --> 00:11:01,100
She made this herself?

172
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:05,500
Yes, Joo Won made every one of them from scratch.

173
00:11:16,110 --> 00:11:17,940
Hello.

174
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:23,360
- Is your elbow better? 
 - Doctor.

175
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:28,300
Hey, Dal. He came in to treat his elbow recently.

176
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:30,650
You remembered me right away.

177
00:11:30,650 --> 00:11:34,020
I remember you were eager about treatment so you could play basketball.

178
00:11:34,020 --> 00:11:35,480
Is it feeling better these days?

179
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:37,290
Are you still doing great at basketball?

180
00:11:37,290 --> 00:11:42,720
Yes, of course. My club just can't run without me.

181
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:46,260
My buddy over there played basketball in America.

182
00:11:46,260 --> 00:11:47,780
A former Haedong High player.

183
00:11:47,780 --> 00:11:50,630
Oh, really? From America?

184
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:53,100
Hello.

185
00:11:53,670 --> 00:11:57,330
It would be great if you guys had time to play a game.

186
00:11:57,330 --> 00:11:59,240
I'm fine whenever.

187
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:01,310
Today works, too.

188
00:12:02,540 --> 00:12:05,370
Then, shall we play a round?

189
00:12:05,370 --> 00:12:07,450
Hurry, Babe.

190
00:12:07,450 --> 00:12:09,200
Hurry over here.

191
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:12,740
The game that will decide Kang Hae Joon's life is about to begin.

192
00:12:12,740 --> 00:12:15,350
Hurry up! Yes!

193
00:12:19,070 --> 00:12:20,580
Oh, thank you.

194
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:22,070
What do you have planned?

195
00:12:22,070 --> 00:12:23,900
The final victory.

196
00:12:23,900 --> 00:12:28,150
Among men, it's over if you lose in a game.

197
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:39,050
What's this?

198
00:12:39,050 --> 00:12:40,670
Why are you here?

199
00:12:40,670 --> 00:12:44,150
Why? Can't I watch Kang Hae Joon play basketball?

200
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:48,190
I haven't been rejected yet.

201
00:12:48,190 --> 00:12:49,730
Fighting.

202
00:12:52,690 --> 00:12:54,640
You should reconsider.

203
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:56,790
You're too good for him.

204
00:12:58,870 --> 00:13:00,930
She has a good eye for people.

205
00:13:00,930 --> 00:13:02,470
Come on!

206
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:04,420
I'll be back.

207
00:13:04,420 --> 00:13:06,310
Be careful.

208
00:13:07,210 --> 00:13:09,060
All right, that's done.

209
00:13:11,550 --> 00:13:14,700
The team that loses will pay for pork belly and soju.

210
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:18,570
- Sounds good. 
 - Why are you making such a big deal?

211
00:13:18,570 --> 00:13:19,850
Just trust me.

212
00:13:19,850 --> 00:13:22,600
I even got my girlfriend's father's approval.

213
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:23,750
What nonsense are you spewing?

214
00:13:23,750 --> 00:13:26,080
Think about it while you do something you love.

215
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,970
Don't regret it.

216
00:13:28,970 --> 00:13:30,460
Fighting.

217
00:13:31,410 --> 00:13:33,320
Fighting.

218
00:13:34,030 --> 00:13:36,470
You know I only settle for first place, right?

219
00:13:38,460 --> 00:13:40,090
Just tighten your shoelaces.

220
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:42,130
- Let's go! 
 - Oppas, do your best!

221
00:13:42,130 --> 00:13:45,100
- Fighting, Babe! 
 - Fighting, Kang Hae Joon!

222
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,760
Let's go.

223
00:13:49,900 --> 00:13:51,810
Hurry and give it to me.

224
00:13:57,720 --> 00:14:00,980
Hey, take him out of here.

225
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:03,880
I'll get it next time.

226
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:07,470
- Oh, hey! 
 - Pass!

227
00:14:07,470 --> 00:14:09,160
Hey, pass!

228
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:16,130
- Hae Joon, let's do this. 
 - Crab! Crab!

229
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:19,650
- Hey, come fast! 
 - Go, first!

230
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:22,700
- Go long! 
 - Is that all you've got?

231
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:24,050
- Come here! Next to me. 
 - Okay.

232
00:14:24,050 --> 00:14:25,220
You can do it.

233
00:14:25,220 --> 00:14:26,900
Go, go!

234
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:31,730
♫  I begin to mirror your smile  ♫

235
00:14:31,730 --> 00:14:33,460
- Kang Hae Joon! 
 - Nice!

236
00:14:33,460 --> 00:14:37,020
- Here. 
 - Okay, I got this.

237
00:14:43,050 --> 00:14:45,140
Nice!

238
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:52,550
♫  I am at my most beautiful when we are together  ♫

239
00:14:52,550 --> 00:14:55,440
♫  So I keep searching for the me reflected in your eyes  ♫

240
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:57,660
Babe, fighting!

241
00:14:59,730 --> 00:15:01,170
Nice!

242
00:15:01,170 --> 00:15:10,290
♫  The fact that someone more precious to me than myself exists  ♫

243
00:15:10,290 --> 00:15:14,850
♫  In this world that remains sorrowful  ♫

244
00:15:14,850 --> 00:15:23,140
♫  It gives me reason to smile  ♫

245
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:41,040
I lost today, so I'll treat you to pork belly.

246
00:15:44,090 --> 00:15:48,400
I don't need pork belly, but let me ask you for a favor.

247
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:52,970
You can ask me anything.

248
00:15:52,970 --> 00:15:54,830
I'll take Dal...

249
00:15:55,530 --> 00:15:57,690
with me today.

250
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:00,270
Pardon?

251
00:16:12,990 --> 00:16:16,740
- Well... 
 - You don't have to say anything.

252
00:16:16,740 --> 00:16:17,800
What?

253
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:22,810
Whatever you say, it doesn't matter to me.

254
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:27,290
No, I...

255
00:16:27,290 --> 00:16:29,610
Let me talk first.

256
00:16:34,740 --> 00:16:37,140
I like you, Sunbae.

257
00:16:37,860 --> 00:16:43,070
No matter how stupid I am, I'm certain of that one thing.

258
00:16:44,940 --> 00:16:48,110
I was told to study, so I did.

259
00:16:48,110 --> 00:16:50,620
I was told to go to law school, so I did.

260
00:16:50,620 --> 00:16:53,570
I was told to become a lawyer, so I did.

261
00:16:53,570 --> 00:17:00,300
There's exactly one thing I did of my own accord.

262
00:17:01,230 --> 00:17:05,850
That was coming down to live in Haedong.

263
00:17:05,850 --> 00:17:11,050
But that wasn't because I love Haedong.

264
00:17:11,050 --> 00:17:16,620
It was because Seoul was too difficult for me.

265
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:23,610
Throughout my life, there weren't many instances

266
00:17:23,610 --> 00:17:27,080
where I thought, "I'll do it" or "I want it,"

267
00:17:27,740 --> 00:17:31,990
just because I liked something.

268
00:17:33,380 --> 00:17:38,170
In high school, you were the first.

269
00:17:39,770 --> 00:17:43,420
The first time I liked anything.

