00:35:25,160 --> 00:35:38,310
♫  I will always, as I have always done, be with you  ♫

533
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:48,610
Where did you go so late last night?

534
00:35:48,610 --> 00:35:50,000
A walk.

535
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:51,820
It was hot, so we took a walk around town.

536
00:35:51,820 --> 00:35:55,710
Why go out when it's hot? You should stay home.

537
00:35:55,710 --> 00:35:59,080
Can I also go on night walks with Joo Won?

538
00:35:59,080 --> 00:36:01,080
Can I?

539
00:36:01,080 --> 00:36:03,080
No way.

540
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:04,370
Why can't we go on walks?

541
00:36:04,370 --> 00:36:07,340
What do you do on your walks?

542
00:36:07,340 --> 00:36:09,380
That's enough.

543
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:14,210
By the way, Dal was so tired in the morning.

544
00:36:14,210 --> 00:36:15,800
Did you walk about 5 km?

545
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:17,810
Gosh, that's enough!

546
00:36:17,810 --> 00:36:21,210
Think about what to do about Mom and Dad.

547
00:36:21,210 --> 00:36:22,930
You said you're going home today, right?

548
00:36:22,930 --> 00:36:24,960
Go talk it out with Dad.

549
00:36:24,960 --> 00:36:27,570
It's the adults' business. Don't be nosy.

550
00:36:27,570 --> 00:36:29,210
It's because they're adults.

551
00:36:29,210 --> 00:36:31,680
They probably can't do a thing because they're mindful of us.

552
00:36:31,680 --> 00:36:35,880
Look at him. The young one does what he needs to do.

553
00:36:37,590 --> 00:36:39,430
I told you to cut it out.

554
00:36:39,430 --> 00:36:40,980
Help me.

555
00:36:40,980 --> 00:36:44,130
- Hey, go easy on her. 
 - Save me...

556
00:36:46,890 --> 00:36:49,090
Why didn't you help?

557
00:36:49,090 --> 00:36:51,650
- You freed yourself. 
 - You still need to help.

558
00:36:51,650 --> 00:36:52,870
I'm sorry.

559
00:36:52,870 --> 00:36:54,620
You still need to save me!

560
00:36:54,620 --> 00:36:56,840
- Okay, okay. 
 - Gosh, when will they grow up?

561
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:58,720
- Mercy. 
 - You promised.

562
00:36:58,720 --> 00:37:01,780
- Hey, wait for me! 
 - Hurry up!

563
00:37:12,560 --> 00:37:14,540
Do you still have things to take from here?

564
00:37:14,540 --> 00:37:18,220
I was reminded of a book I used to read.

565
00:37:20,420 --> 00:37:25,260
Hey... you heard Mom is going to England, right?

566
00:37:25,260 --> 00:37:26,800
Yes.

567
00:37:29,020 --> 00:37:33,180
She comes and goes, all as she pleases.

568
00:37:33,180 --> 00:37:36,310
But I don't think that's the case this time.

569
00:37:37,160 --> 00:37:38,940
Yes, I know.

570
00:37:38,940 --> 00:37:42,370
I should've told you every time

571
00:37:42,370 --> 00:37:46,480
why she was going and coming all those years.

572
00:37:46,480 --> 00:37:48,390
My goodness.

573
00:37:50,060 --> 00:37:52,010
I wasn't able to...

574
00:37:52,010 --> 00:37:55,560
You stayed here, Dad.

575
00:37:55,560 --> 00:38:00,170
You didn't go anywhere and stayed here.

576
00:38:00,170 --> 00:38:03,690
Whether I go away or come back,

577
00:38:03,690 --> 00:38:06,190
you're always here.

578
00:38:06,190 --> 00:38:09,630
And that's why I was okay.

579
00:38:13,890 --> 00:38:16,370
You're late. Hurry up and go now.

580
00:38:16,370 --> 00:38:17,800
Go now.

581
00:38:20,170 --> 00:38:26,540
By the way, Dad, aren't you interested in seeing anyone?

582
00:38:28,050 --> 00:38:30,490
Aigoo, I'm fine. O-Once is enough for me.

583
00:38:30,490 --> 00:38:33,140
Gosh, did I tell you to get married?

584
00:38:33,140 --> 00:38:36,650
You could just have a girlfriend.

585
00:38:36,650 --> 00:38:38,820
Come on...

586
00:38:40,170 --> 00:38:45,720
What? You're telling me to meet someone to watch movies and have coffee together?

587
00:38:45,720 --> 00:38:49,420
Yes. Do what you want to do.

588
00:38:49,420 --> 00:38:53,910
Besides the police station, home, and family.

589
00:38:53,910 --> 00:38:55,920
Think about those things.

590
00:38:55,920 --> 00:38:58,830
How can there be such things? I don't have the time.

591
00:38:58,830 --> 00:39:02,400
It's late. Hurry up and go now! Go on.

592
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:05,400
- I'll go now. See you next time. 
 - Okay.

593
00:39:09,870 --> 00:39:12,820
Yes! It's so nice.

594
00:39:17,690 --> 00:39:20,410
Aigoo, it's so nice!

595
00:39:22,900 --> 00:39:24,990
 Why are you telling me to do nothing? 

596
00:39:24,990 --> 00:39:28,250
Does Ahjusshi have feelings for Ahjumma or not?

597
00:39:28,250 --> 00:39:32,280
- He does. 
 - Would Ahjumma not know when we know?

598
00:39:32,280 --> 00:39:33,780
She probably does.

599
00:39:33,780 --> 00:39:36,480
It shows quite a lot.

600
00:39:37,200 --> 00:39:42,110
But if there hasn't been any progress so far, it means Ahjumma isn't ready.

601
00:39:42,110 --> 00:39:47,250
But if we rush Ahjusshi altogether, how will he feel?

602
00:39:47,250 --> 00:39:49,140
Will he be in a tough spot?

603
00:39:49,790 --> 00:39:50,870
Embarrassed?

604
00:39:50,870 --> 00:39:53,010
I know this because I experienced it.

605
00:39:53,010 --> 00:39:55,500
The most frustrated one isn't us.

606
00:39:55,500 --> 00:39:57,310
It's Ahjusshi.

607
00:39:57,970 --> 00:40:00,590
I feel so sorry for my dad.

608
00:40:00,590 --> 00:40:02,920
I was a pitiful one, too,

609
00:40:04,820 --> 00:40:06,970
when you didn't accept me.

610
00:40:08,530 --> 00:40:11,500
When did I ever say I wouldn't accept you?

611
00:40:11,500 --> 00:40:13,620
You said you wouldn't give me a chance.

612
00:40:13,620 --> 00:40:15,720
Don't you recall?

613
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:18,790
Gosh, you even hold grudges?

614
00:40:21,900 --> 00:40:27,570
♫  Why am I like this?  ♫

615
00:40:29,750 --> 00:40:31,730
 Are you inside? 

616
00:40:32,760 --> 00:40:35,490
Yes, I'm here, too!

617
00:40:38,360 --> 00:40:40,760
- Hey. 
 - Why are you here?

618
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:43,230
We were talking about Dad.

619
00:40:45,420 --> 00:40:47,360
You can talk in the living room.

620
00:40:47,360 --> 00:40:49,660
I'm going. I was about to go.

621
00:40:49,660 --> 00:40:51,260
Bye.

622
00:40:52,770 --> 00:40:54,260
What?

623
00:40:57,230 --> 00:41:00,270
Gosh, do I really have to find a new place?

624
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:24,440
Hello.

625
00:41:30,580 --> 00:41:32,790
Did you come because of your dad?

626
00:41:32,790 --> 00:41:34,310
Yes.

627
00:41:34,310 --> 00:41:37,230
You don't need to be mistaken.

628
00:41:37,230 --> 00:41:41,000
I went to see him a few times because of Hae Joon.

629
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:44,070
Your dad and I don't have any other intention.

630
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:47,220
Back then...

631
00:41:48,250 --> 00:41:51,280
when I said, I didn't need a mom.

632
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:54,700
I think I said that because you were pretty.

633
00:41:56,590 --> 00:42:01,220
I have no memory of my mom, so I only know her from her pictures.

634
00:42:01,220 --> 00:42:05,140
But my mom in her pictures is really pretty.

635
00:42:06,050 --> 00:42:10,460
And when you showed up that day, Ahjumma,

636
00:42:10,460 --> 00:42:13,150
you were really pretty.

637
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:19,540
I don't quite remember because I was too young.

638
00:42:19,540 --> 00:42:22,650
But I remember I was mad because you were pretty...

639
00:42:23,240 --> 00:42:24,950
and...

640
00:42:26,590 --> 00:42:32,860
I remember I was mad because of the way Dad looked at you.

641
00:42:35,580 --> 00:42:38,520
Reflecting on it after I grew up,

642
00:42:38,520 --> 00:42:43,260
I don't think Dad ever looked at anyone the same way.

643
00:42:45,250 --> 00:42:48,370
I probably won't ever get to have

644
00:42:48,370 --> 00:42:53,430
a mom again in my life if it isn't you.

645
00:42:54,100 --> 00:42:57,190
Could you be my mom, please?

646
00:42:57,190 --> 00:42:59,500
I'll be a good daughter.

647
00:43:15,830 --> 00:43:19,100
You'll ruin your shoulder like that.

648
00:43:19,100 --> 00:43:20,860
Tiring your body out

649
00:43:20,860 --> 00:43:24,250
just because your mind is cluttered is for when you're young.

650
00:43:24,250 --> 00:43:28,770
You need to be wary of your age now, Mr. Yoon.

651
00:43:29,380 --> 00:43:32,190
I think I'll do radish noodles this summer, too.

652
00:43:32,190 --> 00:43:35,570
Last year, quite a lot of people were asking about it.

653
00:43:36,760 --> 00:43:38,400
I won't do it.

654
00:43:38,400 --> 00:43:40,270
You can hire someone,

655
00:43:40,270 --> 00:43:44,640
or you can get married and make your wife do it.

656
00:43:44,640 --> 00:43:46,610
But I won't do it.

657
00:43:46,610 --> 00:43:48,900
Well, should I go on a blind date

658
00:43:48,900 --> 00:43:51,360
and say that I need to get married because I need someone

659
00:43:51,360 --> 00:43:54,700
to make summer radish kimchi for me?

660
00:43:54,700 --> 00:43:57,070
What? Should I?

661
00:43:57,070 --> 00:43:58,990
My goodness.

662
00:44:10,620 --> 00:44:13,000
Madam, as I was saying, go to the marketplace

663
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:15,700
and check out the summer radish.

664
00:44:15,700 --> 00:44:19,300
O-Oh, yes. Aigoo.

665
00:44:20,610 --> 00:44:22,050
I'm not going.

666
00:44:22,050 --> 00:44:25,800
I'm just going to go home.

667
00:44:28,850 --> 00:44:31,030
Summer radish noodles?

668
00:44:32,430 --> 00:44:34,330
Why don't you try?

669
00:44:38,520 --> 00:44:41,330
- Take a seat. 
 - Yes.

670
00:44:50,470 --> 00:44:52,410
What brings you here today?

671
00:44:52,410 --> 00:44:56,420
Did Hae Joon say something again?

672
00:44:56,420 --> 00:45:00,180
I don't know how to make summer radish kimchi.

673
00:45:00,180 --> 00:45:02,370
Sorry?

674
00:45:02,370 --> 00:45:03,970
But...

675
00:45:04,710 --> 00:45:06,520
I'll still try to learn how.

676
00:45:07,240 --> 00:45:09,970
What do you mean?

677
00:45:09,970 --> 00:45:12,810
I'll try to learn

678
00:45:12,810 --> 00:45:15,370
how to keep a home,

679
00:45:16,170 --> 00:45:20,040
make noodles, and raise a daughter, too.

680
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:41,200
I asked you not to make things uncomfortable for me.

681
00:45:42,530 --> 00:45:45,360
But I'm being too shameless, right?

682
00:45:46,940 --> 00:45:52,380
I was always wayward with you, Jeong Jae.

683
00:45:52,380 --> 00:45:55,250
I shouldn't have done that.

684
00:45:55,250 --> 00:45:56,650
I'm sorry.

685
00:45:56,650 --> 00:45:59,070
Y-You see...

686
00:46:04,920 --> 00:46:11,040
You see, I had feelings for you from the first day you came here.

687
00:46:16,250 --> 00:46:20,100
A single father having feelings isn't a big deal.

688
00:46:21,020 --> 00:46:24,070
So I just put it aside and went on with life.

689
00:46:24,070 --> 00:46:27,080
But those feelings returned after I saw you again.

690
00:46:32,200 --> 00:46:39,510
I doubted my heart would race again at this age,

691
00:46:39,510 --> 00:46:41,530
but it does indeed race.

692
00:46:46,080 --> 00:46:48,820
Gosh, you know...

693
00:46:52,520 --> 00:46:56,110
You don't need to learn how to make kimchi or do house chores.

694
00:47:06,190 --> 00:47:08,110
Let's just...

695
00:47:09,240 --> 00:47:12,260
laugh and cry together.

696
00:47:13,400 --> 00:47:15,810
Let's just live like that.

697
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:42,810
Hey, let's turn it this way.

698
00:47:42,810 --> 00:47:44,990
Lift it. One, two, three!

699
00:47:44,990 --> 00:47:48,330
I mean, let's just put it back where it was.

700
00:47:48,330 --> 00:47:51,290
Still, we should switch up the new sofa and the bed placement to

701
00:47:51,290 --> 00:47:53,790
make it feel like a newlywed's home.

702
00:47:53,790 --> 00:47:57,510
That's why we should redo the walls and get them new furniture.

703
00:47:57,510 --> 00:48:00,780
Hey, I'll take care of it.

704
00:48:00,780 --> 00:48:02,610
You should stop coming over!

705
00:48:02,610 --> 00:48:05,710
Dad, just getting a new sofa won't make it feel like a newlywed's home.

706
00:48:05,710 --> 00:48:07,020
That one.

707
00:48:07,020 --> 00:48:10,010
That one lived in Haedong longer than Kim San Ha.

708
00:48:10,010 --> 00:48:12,900
Reminds me of the old days. I like it.

709
00:48:12,900 --> 00:48:15,940
Where did Ahjusshi go? Isn't it his day off?

710
00:48:15,940 --> 00:48:19,130
♪ I love you ♪

711
00:48:19,130 --> 00:48:23,220
   

712
00:48:23,220 --> 00:48:29,550
♪ I love you so much ♪

713
00:48:33,130 --> 00:48:34,800
Mr. Kim.

714
00:48:34,800 --> 00:48:38,130
How is your singing so full of emotion?

715
00:48:38,130 --> 00:48:40,270
It's Chief Kim, not Mr. Kim.

716
00:48:40,270 --> 00:48:43,100
- He's the senior inspector of our town. 
 - Yes.

717
00:48:43,100 --> 00:48:45,890
My gosh, how do you sing so well?

718
00:48:45,890 --> 00:48:47,180
A-Aigoo, not at all.

719
00:48:47,180 --> 00:48:48,990
- Please excuse me– 
 - Hold on.

720
00:48:48,990 --> 00:48:52,130
We are getting some iced coffee right here. Join us.

721
00:48:52,130 --> 00:48:55,210
Oh, my kids are waiting for me at home.

722
00:48:55,210 --> 00:48:58,280
Aigoo, I'm sorry. Next time.

723
00:48:59,790 --> 00:49:02,370
So he doesn't even go to singing classes anymore?

724
00:49:02,370 --> 00:49:07,800
I mean, it's weird enough for me that Dad is singing in front of people.

725
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:12,920
You only went to the hiking club twice and stopped going.

726
00:49:13,440 --> 00:49:21,620
Back then, I went because they said the makgeolli (rice wine) tasted great after hiking.

727
00:49:21,620 --> 00:49:25,590
But the mountain was quite high.

728
00:49:27,770 --> 00:49:32,100
Of course, a mountain is high. What will it be otherwise?

729
00:49:32,100 --> 00:49:35,120
So, is your wedding all ready to go?

730
00:49:35,120 --> 00:49:37,320
Gosh, don't call it a wedding.

731
00:49:37,320 --> 00:49:40,090
We are just gathering for a meal.

732
00:49:40,090 --> 00:49:42,430
He's just embarrassed.

733
00:49:42,430 --> 00:49:46,190
Dad, so... what will you...

734
00:49:46,190 --> 00:49:47,670
what will you do now? Hurry up and decide.

735
00:49:47,670 --> 00:49:50,330
J-Just say the final verdict here.

736
00:49:50,330 --> 00:49:52,040
How about aerobics? It's right around the corner.

737
00:49:52,040 --> 00:49:54,050
Yes, that sounds great.

738
00:49:54,050 --> 00:49:56,440
- I thought about it... 
 - Yes.

739
00:49:56,440 --> 00:49:58,030
How does cooking sound?

740
00:49:58,030 --> 00:49:59,910
- No way. Not at all. 
 - What?

741
00:49:59,910 --> 00:50:01,470
- I-I can teach you. 
 - Don't you dare.

742
00:50:01,470 --> 00:50:03,450
- I'm not doing it. 
 - You should stick to baking cakes.

743
00:50:03,450 --> 00:50:04,720
I'm really good, though.

744
00:50:04,720 --> 00:50:06,680
I'm not doing it.

745
00:50:09,590 --> 00:50:12,210
- The cake store there disappeared? 
 - Yes.

746
00:50:12,210 --> 00:50:14,930
I told you last time.

747
00:50:14,930 --> 00:50:16,520
When?

748
00:50:16,520 --> 00:50:18,290
Right after you came back to Haedong.

749
00:50:18,290 --> 00:50:20,990
We were eating ice cream together.

750
00:50:22,590 --> 00:50:25,130
You don't remember that?

751
00:50:27,400 --> 00:50:30,310
You really must not listen to what I say.

752
00:50:32,340 --> 00:50:35,450
Back then, I was a bit bewitched by someone.

753
00:50:35,450 --> 00:50:37,350
Forget it.

754
00:50:37,980 --> 00:50:40,360
- Let's go. 
 - Where?

755
00:50:42,690 --> 00:50:45,120
I wanted to try this.

756
00:50:45,120 --> 00:50:46,470
Do you even know how to do it?

757
00:50:46,470 --> 00:50:48,380
It's my first time.

758
00:50:48,380 --> 00:50:49,680
You don't even know how to do it. 
    

759
00:50:49,680 --> 00:50:51,190
- There you go. 
 - Yes.

760
00:50:51,190 --> 00:50:53,170
- All right. 
 - Wh-Where?

761
00:50:53,170 --> 00:50:55,920
No, it's not this. It's there.

762
00:50:55,920 --> 00:50:57,940
Oh, it's there.

763
00:50:57,940 --> 00:50:59,840
One, two, three.

764
00:51:03,330 --> 00:51:04,960
Growl.

765
00:51:05,650 --> 00:51:12,880
♫  In the breeze, in the moonlight, a softly whispered prayer is carried  ♫

766
00:51:12,880 --> 00:51:15,920
- This one came out well. 
 - It did.

767
00:51:15,920 --> 00:51:18,290
You look good with a crown.

768
00:51:19,270 --> 00:51:22,030
You look too natural, though, Yoon Joo Won.

769
00:51:22,030 --> 00:51:24,410
Because it's with you, Oppa.

770
00:51:25,830 --> 00:51:27,020
It's pretty.

771
00:51:27,020 --> 00:51:28,360
   

772
00:51:29,500 --> 00:51:31,750
-  Oppa.  
 - Yes.

773
00:51:31,750 --> 00:51:33,560
 Did you think about it? 

774
00:51:33,560 --> 00:51:35,340
 Is it really impossible? 

775
00:51:35,340 --> 00:51:38,180
I'm sorry. I'll be there in the fall.

776
00:51:38,180 --> 00:51:41,970
Your school and accommodation are ready, so don't worry about them.

777
00:51:41,970 --> 00:51:45,090
Yes. I'll see you at the airport.

778
00:51:47,870 --> 00:51:50,320
When is she leaving?

779
00:51:50,320 --> 00:51:51,850
Next week.

780
00:51:51,850 --> 00:51:53,980
Will you be okay?

781
00:51:53,980 --> 00:51:55,690
With what?

782
00:51:55,690 --> 00:51:59,010
Are you really okay with not dropping her off?

783
00:52:00,630 --> 00:52:02,530
So Hui's still young

784
00:52:02,530 --> 00:52:05,710
and Ahjumma still has difficulty walking.

785
00:52:06,360 --> 00:52:08,360
We need to prepare for the wedding, too.

786
00:52:08,360 --> 00:52:10,400
I'm not okay with this.

787
00:52:10,400 --> 00:52:13,300
It's obvious when you're worried, Oppa.

788
00:52:13,880 --> 00:52:16,440
Take the trip. Okay?

789
00:52:17,970 --> 00:52:21,400
If it bothers you, you can buy a gift on the way back.

790
00:52:21,400 --> 00:52:22,970
"A gift"?

791
00:52:24,560 --> 00:52:26,420
What will you buy?

